      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model inputs (geometry tolerances, fluid properties, boundary conditions) must be characterized with documented sources and nominal uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "All model inputs were characterized: pump geometry from manufacturer drawings (±0.05 mm tolerance), blood-analog viscosity from rheometer measurements (±2%), inlet velocity profiles from Doppler ultrasound (±3%). Input uncertainty bounds documented and propagated through a Monte Carlo sampling scheme of 200 runs to generate output distribution for the hemolysis index. A screening sensitivity study was conducted as part of the UQ workflow, identifying rotational speed and inlet hematocrit as the largest contributors to output variance; however, the structured sensitivity analysis record has not been separately encoded as a linked artifact in this package."
    },
